		<div id="comment-4322">
			<cite class="fn">Bob</cite>			<a href="http://bloodyshovel.wordpress.com/2014/02/08/monarchy-and-monarchs/#comment-4322">February 10, 2014 at 05:09</a>
						<div class="comment-body"><p>Yes linguists make this point although I&#8217;m not sure I agree. They argue that the characters are technically just morphemes. But words are technically one or more morphemes, and single morphemes, and consequently characters, tend to be words in Chinese. Furthermore, Chinese, specifically written Chinese, is flexible enough where you can use and treat a single character, which normally would be used as part of a multiple morpheme word, as a separate, independent word itself.</p>
</div>

			<div class="reply">
				<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2014/02/08/monarchy-and-monarchs/?replytocom=4322#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-4322", "4322", "respond", "1578")'>Reply</a>			</div>
