	<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-spandrell9 bypostauthor even depth-6 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-4323">
		<div id="comment-4323">
			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://bloodyshovel.wordpress.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>spandrell</a></cite>			<a href="http://bloodyshovel.wordpress.com/2014/02/08/monarchy-and-monarchs/#comment-4323">February 10, 2014 at 05:23</a>
						<div class="comment-body"><p>Characters were words in the classical language but it&#8217;s hard to say that for modern mandarin.<br />
Still given that literacy gives you access to the classical language, changing the script would cut that connections, potentially breaking most idioms and educated speech.</p>
</div>

			<div class="reply">
				<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2014/02/08/monarchy-and-monarchs/?replytocom=4323#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-4323", "4323", "respond", "1578")'>Reply</a>			</div>
		</div>
